srv  log_server_r: request:  {"prompt": "You are a senior infrastructure engineer at a small startup. The team has been running a llama.cpp server on an old AMD Vega 64 graphics card via the Vulkan backend, and you have been asked to write a short incident summary for today's minor outage. Around 14:30 the primary inference endpoint started returning 503 responses for roughly eight minutes. The oncall person restarted the llama-server process and traffic recovered. The hypothesis is that a long context request from an automated summarisation job triggered a VRAM allocation failure which took the process down. You have access to logs from the affected time window, the server's VRAM breakdown trace, and a list of the three clients that were sending requests during the window. Write the incident summary as a numbered list with five entries: detection, impact, root-cause hypothesis, immediate remediation, and follow-up work. Keep it concise and factual, no blame language, no exaggeration of severity. Include one concrete follow-up action the team can verify within a week. Do not use any tool calls; just answer in plain text.\n", "n_predict": 256, "temperature": 0, "seed": 42, "stream": false, "cache_prompt": false}
